Forty years from now, I would anticipate we'll be

00:10.227 --> 00:16.859
below a million barrels of black oil per day. Gas 
production, currently we're running about 17

00:17.700 --> 00:21.787
trillion cubic feet a year. I would not be 
surprised 40 years from now, that we may still be at

00:25.310 --> 00:28.913
14, 15 trillion cubic feet a year. We do have a 
pretty fair gas reserve that's left unexplored.

00:33.677 --> 00:37.481
But black oil, we're essentially out of black oil 
reserves. People say that you can't deplete oil.

00:41.044 --> 00:42.345
